nne","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["variant of   Anne  , in common use as a given name in most European languages. Among people with a classical education, it has from time to time been associated with  Virgil's  Aeneid, where it is borne by the sister of  Dido , Queen of Carthage. This Phoenician name may ultimately be of Semitic origin, and thus related to the biblical <i>Anne</i>. However, the connection, if it exists, is indirect rather than direct."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Anne Sterling was born in 1580, in Hartest, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. She married Thomas Griggs in 1598, in Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 4 sons and 2 daughters. She died on 20 March 1637, in her hometown, at the age of 57, and was buried in Hartest, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1580–20 March 1637":"1580–20. märts 1637","1569–1605":"1569–1605","1598–1646":"1598–1646","1599–Male":"1599–Surnud","1600–1676":"1600–1676","1602–Female":"1602–Surnud","1603–1669":"1603–1669","1605–Male":"1605–Surnud","1580–1637":"1580–1637","chr 1602":"1602","18 September 1605":"18. september 1605","20 March 1637":"20. märts 1637","1580":"1580","1 March 1605":"1. märts 1605","chr. 13 Sep 1598":"13. september 1598","1602":"1602","1646":"1646","1569":"1569","1600":"1600","chr. 1599":"1599","1676":"1676","1599":"1599","1598":"1598","1605":"1605","1637":"1637","1603":"1603","1669":"1669","Hartest, Suffolk, England":"Hartest, Suffolk, England","Hartest, Suffolk, Eng.":"Hartest, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","Hartest, Babergh District, Suffolk, England":"Hartest, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","All Saints Churchyard Hartest, Babergh District, Suffolk, England":"Hartest, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1580–20 March 1637":"1580–20. maaliskuuta 1637","1569–1605":"1569–1605","1598–1646":"1598–1646","1599–Male"